üìò Security Concepts ‚Äì PG-DITISS (Aug 2025)
Session 22: Android Debug Bridge (ADB) & Mobile Penetration Testing Tools
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Android Debug Bridge (ADB) is a:
A. Programming language
B. Command-line tool
C. Mobile OS
D. Antivirus

2. ADB is mainly used to communicate with:
A. Web servers
B. Android devices/emulators
C. Network switches
D. Databases

3. ADB works in which mode by default?
A. GUI mode
B. Client‚Äìserver mode
C. Peer-to-peer
D. Offline mode

4. Which command lists connected Android devices?
A. adb start
B. adb devices
C. adb connect
D. adb install

5. Android Emulator is commonly used with ADB for:
A. Hardware repair
B. App testing and debugging
C. Network routing
D. Disk encryption

6. ADB can be used to:
A. Install applications
B. Uninstall applications
C. Access device shell
D. All of the above

7. Mobile penetration testing tools are used to:
A. Develop apps
B. Identify mobile security vulnerabilities
C. Increase performance
D. Encrypt devices

8. ADB is part of which Android component?
A. Android SDK
B. Android Kernel
C. Google Play
D. Android BIOS

9. Which OS supports ADB usage?
A. Linux only
B. Windows only
C. macOS only
D. Windows, Linux, and macOS

10. Enabling USB debugging allows:
A. Faster charging
B. ADB access to device
C. Root access
D. App encryption

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. ADB uses which port by default for communication?
A. 21
B. 80
C. 5037
D. 8080

12. Which ADB command installs an APK file?
A. adb shell
B. adb push
C. adb install
D. adb pull

13. ADB shell command provides:
A. GUI access
B. Command-line access to device
C. Network scan
D. File encryption

14. Leaving USB debugging enabled is risky because it:
A. Slows device
B. Allows unauthorized device access
C. Uses more battery
D. Breaks apps

15. Mobile penetration testing tools usually test:
A. Hardware faults
B. App permissions and insecure storage
C. Screen resolution
D. Battery usage

16. Which ADB command copies files from device to PC?
A. adb push
B. adb pull
C. adb install
D. adb connect

17. ADB over Wi-Fi increases risk because it:
A. Uses encryption
B. Exposes debugging interface over network
C. Improves speed
D. Requires root

18. Which scenario shows misuse of ADB?
A. App debugging by developer
B. Unauthorized data extraction from device
C. Emulator testing
D. App deployment

19. Penetration testing tools for Android are often used with:
A. Antivirus
B. Emulators and test devices
C. Routers
D. Switches

20. ADB helps pentesters mainly during:
A. Planning phase
B. Post-exploitation and analysis
C. Risk assessment
D. Reporting only

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10) ‚Äì CCEE TRAP ZONE
21. Why ADB is considered a security risk on production devices?
A. Uses high CPU
B. Allows deep system interaction
C. Consumes battery
D. Slows apps

22. Which attack becomes easier if ADB is exposed?
A. DoS
B. Data exfiltration
C. DNS spoofing
D. MAC flooding

23. ADB access WITHOUT rooting still allows:
A. Kernel modification
B. App installation and file access (limited)
C. Full system control
D. BIOS changes

24. Best practice for secure Android devices is to:
A. Enable ADB always
B. Disable USB debugging in production
C. Use emulator only
D. Root device

25. Mobile pentesting tools combined with ADB help attackers to:
A. Improve UI
B. Automate testing and exploitation
C. Increase battery life
D. Encrypt OS

26. Which security principle is violated if ADB is misused?
A. Availability
B. Confidentiality
C. Performance
D. Scalability

27. ADB command execution requires:
A. Internet access
B. Authorized device pairing
C. Antivirus disabled
D. Root access

28. Using emulator for ADB labs is preferred because it:
A. Is faster than real phone
B. Prevents damage to real device
C. Is insecure
D. Requires rooting

29. ADB-based attacks are MOST effective when device is:
A. Locked and encrypted
B. USB debugging enabled and unlocked
C. Powered off
D. Updated

30. Session 22 mainly tests understanding of:
A. Mobile UI design
B. Android debugging & mobile pentesting basics
C. Hardware troubleshooting
D. Database security

